  "signature": "ed25519:b4e2a1f3c7d09581fb6b2e4d5c9a73e1f2b6d4c0a3e8f5b7c2d1a4e0f9b3c6d2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) operates under an FDA-recognized quality management system (ISO 13485); solver version control and regression test suite documented in DePuy Synthes SOPs. Gradation 2 required because model influence is Medium and decision consequence is Medium; Gradation 3 achieved through full IQ/OQ/PQ records and independent code-to-code benchmarking.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is used under a validated software environment with ISO 13485 QMS controls. IQ/OQ/PQ records are on file. Independent code-to-code benchmarks against Abaqus 2021 for a representative beam-bending problem confirm agreement within 0.3%. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must reproduce ASME V&V 10 benchmark problems for linear elasticity and contact to within 1% of analytical solution. Gradation 2 required given Medium model risk level; achieved through documented patch-test results and manufacturer verification reports.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical passes standard ASME V&V 10 patch tests for linear elasticity. Contact algorithm verified against Hertzian contact benchmark with 0.8% error. Manufacturer verification documentation (Ansys VVR-2022-R2) on file. Required Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate <2% change in all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) between the production mesh and a uniformly refined mesh. Gradation 3 required because contact-dominated regions exhibit steep stress gradients near the pedicle screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted. Element edge length was halved from coarse (1.0 mm) to medium (0.5 mm) to fine (0.25 mm) in the screw shank and rod contact zones. QoI changes between medium and fine meshes: stiffness 0.9%, yield force 1.4%, force at 40 mm 1.1%. Production mesh corresponds to the fine level. Gradation 3 criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear solver residual must converge below 1e-4 force norm for all load increments; energy criterion below 1e-6. Gradation 2 required for quasi-static nonlinear analysis with frictional contact at Medium model risk.",
      "rationale": "All load steps converged with force residual below 1e-5 and energy criterion below 1e-7. No divergence or excessive bisection events observed across 11 specimen simulations. Solver log files archived. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup must be independently reviewed by a second qualified analyst; boundary condition application and material assignment verified against a pre-approved simulation template. Gradation 2 required for Medium model influence.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior FEA analyst reviewed the model setup checklist, boundary condition assignments, and material property tables prior to execution. Discrepancies were documented and resolved. No critical use errors identified. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic model with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity must be justified by material coupon data; frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.2) must be supported by published tribology data for Ti-6Al-4V on Ti-6Al-4V interfaces. Gradation 3 required because plasticity governs yield force prediction, a primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material response modeled as bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.2 GPa) consistent with ASTM F136 coupon data from the same material lot. Frictional contact coefficient mu=0.2 drawn from published literature for dry Ti-Ti interfaces. Model form assumptions documented in the simulation report. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Geometric inputs must be derived from CMM measurements of the as-manufactured hardware used in bench testing; material inputs must be traceable to lot-specific coupon tests or certified material data sheets. Gradation 3 required because geometric tolerances in the pedicle screw thread profile directly affect stiffness QoI.",
      "rationale": "CAD geometry was updated from CMM measurements of the actual test hardware (tolerance ±0.01 mm). Material certificates for Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM F136) and UHMWPE spacer blocks provided by DePuy Synthes. Input uncertainty propagated via ±1 SD Monte Carlo (n=500); QoI sensitivity to geometric variation confirmed below 3%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens required to characterize inter-specimen variability; specimens must be from production-representative lots with documented traceability. Gradation 3 required because specimen-to-specimen geometric variation is a known source of QoI scatter in F1717 testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens from the same production lot with full traceability documentation. Inter-specimen CoV for stiffness 4.2%, yield force 3.8%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (6° offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one loading configuration was evaluated; multi-angle or multi-rate conditions were not included due to resource constraints. The required Gradation 3 calls for at least two distinct test conditions to bound the model's predictive range, but only one condition was achieved (Gradation 2). This shortfall is noted as a limitation of the current validation campaign; the gap is accepted given that the single F1717 condition is the regulatory standard condition and model predictions at this condition are within the 10% tolerance bound."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All FEA boundary conditions and loading parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test setup; any deviations must be quantified and their effect on QoIs bounded. Gradation 2 required for Medium model influence.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry (6° offset, fixed inferior block, displacement-controlled superior loading). Load application point and constraint locations verified against laboratory fixture drawings. Crosshead compliance measured and excluded from displacement data. Equivalency confirmed; Gradation 3 achieved through documented fixture-to-model dimensional comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison must use the ASME V&V 10.1 validation metric E/uval for each QoI; E/uval < 1.96 required for all three QoIs. Percentage difference must also be below 10% for each QoI. Gradation 3 required because three distinct QoIs are compared and uncertainty quantification must account for both model and experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 10.1: stiffness 0.87, yield force 1.23, force at 40 mm 1.41. All three below the 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences: stiffness 4.1%, yield force 7.3%, force at 40 mm 6.8%. All below 10% bound. Combined validation metric satisfies Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) must be directly linked to the regulatory submission requirement and to clinically relevant failure modes. Gradation 3 required because all three QoIs appear in the 510(k) substantial equivalence comparison.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the exact metrics specified in the FDA guidance for ASTM F1717 submissions and directly correspond to clinical failure modes (excessive deformation, permanent set, catastrophic fracture). QoI relevance is fully established. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same hardware geometry, material lot, and test standard as the intended COU; any differences between validation conditions and COU conditions must be explicitly documented and bounded. Gradation 3 required for Medium model risk level and Medium decision consequence.",
      "rationale": "Validation hardware is production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from the same design family as the COU device. Test standard (ASTM F1717) is identical to the regulatory submission requirement. Differences between validation and COU (in-vivo vs. bench environment, absence of biological tissue) are documented and considered acceptable given the conservative nature of the F1717 test. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
  ],
